# React: Lazy Loading Images and Components

This rule defines how to lazily load images and components to improve performance and interactivity. It provides a shared `LazyImage` component and a `lazyComponent` helper to standardize usage.

## Images
Always prefer lazy loading for non-critical images.

Minimum standard:
- Use `<img loading="lazy" decoding="async">` for all non-critical images.

Preferred standard:
- Use the shared `LazyImage` component which enforces sensible defaults and offers placeholders.

Props suggestions for `LazyImage`:
- `src`, `alt` (required)
- `width`, `height` (recommended to avoid CLS)
- `className`, `style`
- `placeholder` (optional node or data URI)

## Components
Use code splitting for heavy or rarely-used components, such as dialogs, charts, and large editors.

Helper: `lazyComponent`
- Wrap `React.lazy` and `Suspense` with a consistent fallback API.
- Example:
  ```tsx
  const MergeReviewDialog = lazyComponent(
    () => import('@/components/events/MergeReviewDialog'),
    { fallback: <div className="p-4">Cargando…</div> }
  );
  ```

Guidelines:
- Route-level code splitting is encouraged for large sections.
- For small, frequently used components, avoid lazy to reduce Suspense boundaries overhead.
- Prefer stable `fallback` UIs that match surrounding layout to avoid layout shifts.

## Directory and naming
- `apps/admin/src/components/LazyImage.tsx`
- `apps/admin/src/components/lazyComponent.ts`

## Examples in this codebase
- `MergeReviewDialog` in `apps/admin/src/routes/events/index.tsx` can be lazy-loaded.
- Replace direct `<img>` usages with `LazyImage` where appropriate.

### Component lazy example
```tsx
// apps/admin/src/routes/events/index.tsx (excerpt)
import { lazyComponent } from '@/components/lazyComponent';

const MergeReviewDialog = lazyComponent(
  () => import('@/components/events/MergeReviewDialog'),
  { fallback: <div className="p-4">Cargando…</div> }
);
```

### Image lazy example
```tsx
// apps/admin/src/components/events/EventsTable.tsx (excerpt)
import LazyImage from '@/components/LazyImage';

function EventRow({ posterUrl, title }: { posterUrl: string; title: string }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <LazyImage
        src={posterUrl}
        alt={title}
        width={64}
        height={64}
        className="rounded"
        placeholder={<div className="w-16 h-16 bg-muted animate-pulse rounded" />}
      />
      <span>{title}</span>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## PR checklist
- Non-critical images use `loading="lazy"` and `decoding="async"` (or `LazyImage`).
- Heavy/rare components are lazy-loaded with `lazyComponent`.
- Fallback UIs are provided and visually stable.
- Width/height provided for images where possible.

